\doTocEntry\toclof{1}{\csname a:TocLink\endcsname{1}{x1-10041}{}{\ignorespaces P/D-isochron diagrams for a synthetic dataset generated using the procedures of Appendix\nobreakspace  {}\o:ref {app:syntheticdata}. The true slope and intercept are $a=1$ and $b=1$ for the conventional isochrons (i--iii), and $a=1$ and $b=-1$ for the inverse isochrons (iv--vi). These parameter values correspond to $[D/d]_0=[D/P]^{\ast }=1$. The true trends are shown as dashed lines and the estimated trends as solid lines, with 95\% confidence envelopes shown in grey. The estimated parameter values are shown above the panels. Unconstrained isochron regression (i and iv) yields imprecise and inaccurate results. Fixing the inherited component (ii and v) or the radiogenic component (iii and vi) greatly improves both aspects of the fit.}}{figure}\relax 
